# Taloo UI Design Guidelines

## Design Philosophy
- **Minimal**: No heavy borders or shadows. Use subtle backgrounds instead.
- **Clean**: Generous whitespace, clear hierarchy.
- **Color accents**: Use brand colors sparingly for emphasis.

## Brand Color Palette (Tailwind utilities)
```
bg-brand-blue       (#015AD9) - Primary actions, selected states
bg-brand-light-blue (#7BC9EE) - Subtle highlights, labels on dark
bg-brand-dark-blue  (#022641) - Dark backgrounds, cards
bg-brand-lime-green (#CDFE00) - Accent buttons, highlights on dark
bg-brand-pink       (#E51399) - Secondary accent, delete hover states
```

### Color Usage
- **Primary buttons**: `bg-brand-blue text-white` or `bg-brand-lime-green text-brand-dark-blue`
- **Dark sections**: `bg-brand-dark-blue` with `text-white` and `text-brand-light-blue` for labels
- **Switches/toggles**: Use `green-600` (not lime-green) for active states - it's more readable
- **Count badges**: `bg-green-100 text-green-600` for active counts
- **Icon backgrounds**: Use solid brand colors (`bg-brand-blue`, `bg-brand-pink`, `bg-gray-900`)

## Spacing
- Use `space-y-6` or `space-y-10` for section spacing
- Use `pb-3` or `mb-3` for label-to-content spacing
- Use `gap-2` or `gap-3` for button groups
- Use `p-6` for card padding
- Center content with `max-w-3xl mx-auto`

## Borders & Shadows
- **Avoid**: Heavy borders, box shadows
- **Use**: `border border-gray-100` for subtle card definition
- **Use**: `rounded-xl` or `rounded-2xl` for cards
- **Use**: `rounded-lg` for buttons and smaller elements

## Component Patterns

### Cards/Sections
```tsx
<div className="rounded-xl bg-gray-50/50 border border-gray-100">
```

### Dark Input Sections
```tsx
<div className="bg-brand-dark-blue rounded-2xl p-6 space-y-6">
  <Text className="text-white">Title</Text>
  <Text size="1" className="text-brand-light-blue uppercase tracking-wide">Label</Text>
  <Input className="bg-white/10 border-0 text-white placeholder:text-white/40" />
  <Button className="bg-brand-lime-green text-brand-dark-blue">Action</Button>
</div>
```

### Toggle Buttons (Agent/Category selectors)
```tsx
// Selected state
className="bg-white text-brand-dark-blue"
// Unselected state (on dark)
className="bg-white/10 text-white/80 hover:bg-white/20"
// Unselected state (on light)
className="bg-gray-50 text-gray-600 hover:bg-gray-100"
```

### Icon Badges
```tsx
<div className="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-brand-blue flex items-center justify-center">
  <Icon className="w-4 h-4 text-white" />
</div>
```

### List Items with Hover
```tsx
<div className="py-3 px-3 rounded-lg transition-colors group hover:bg-white">
  {/* Delete button only shows on hover */}
  <Button className="opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity">
</div>
```

## Typography
- Use Radix UI `<Text>` and `<Heading>` components
- Labels: `size="1"` with `text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wide`
- Body: `size="2"` with `text-foreground` or `text-gray-500`
- Secondary text: `text-gray-400`

## Icons
- Use `lucide-react` icons
- Avoid: Stars, brains, sparkles (too flashy)
- Prefer: Simple, functional icons (Layers, Phone, MessageSquare, Settings, etc.)

## What NOT to Do
- Don't use heavy shadows (`shadow-md`, `shadow-lg`)
- Don't use thick borders (`border-2`)
- Don't use lime-green for text or UI elements that need readability
- Don't add emojis unless explicitly requested
- Don't use gradient backgrounds (except subtle ones like `bg-gray-50/50`)
